snippet.textDisplay: not that you'll ever read this but I figured I'd give some tips, I am a cosmetologist trying to look out for my homies that want to experiment with their hair at home. some sally products are professional grade, but most are not, and most of the bleach and color products they sell contain metals in it that if you arent careful enough or read the ingredients carefully you could damage the FREAK out of your hair. Also, the way you apply the bleach you want to go in a downward motion preferably with a dyeing brush, because rubbing your hair like that opens and roughens your hair cuticle, and breaks your hair. BUT SARAH, let your hair rest for a while, you did too much cooking and she needs a little break and maybe some cute conditioner masks, let her grow a little too. and PLEASE DO A GAMING VIDEO!<3
snippet.textOriginal: not that you'll ever read this but I figured I'd give some tips, I am a cosmetologist trying to look out for my homies that want to experiment with their hair at home. some sally products are professional grade, but most are not, and most of the bleach and color products they sell contain metals in it that if you arent careful enough or read the ingredients carefully you could damage the FREAK out of your hair. Also, the way you apply the bleach you want to go in a downward motion preferably with a dyeing brush, because rubbing your hair like that opens and roughens your hair cuticle, and breaks your hair.
